name: Sweet Corn Puree
description: The recommended portion size of lean protein eg chicken breast meat for a main meal is 100-150g. This is a guide only, the exact amount depends on many factors including body weight, age, gender, height and how active you are.

name: Tuna baked potatoes
description: There's nothing more comforting than a hot baked potato for your evening meal. Just add a topping of tuna and cheese, and tuck in!

name: Low GI banana bread
description: Transform your overripe bananas into something deliciously sweet, moist and healthy! This banana bread is perfect for an afternoon snack with a cup of tea, or enjoy a slice toasted with your morning coffee

name: Sweet n sour chicken
description: Enjoy this fakeaway. It is a cheaper, lower sugar alternative to the takeaway version and the meat is stir-fried instead of deep fried, making it a much healthier choice. What's not to love?

name: Spicy Orange Barbeque Pork
description: Quick and simple, this dish makes the perfect mid-week dinner. Marinate lean pork steaks in herbs and spices for an hour, then pop on the barbeque or fry in a pan, and finish with a tangy orange sauce. Just the right amount of sweetness and spice to give your taste buds a treat

name: hot cross buns
description: Made with wholemeal flour, these mini hot cross buns are smaller in size for a better portion control.
